title: High School Football: Week 7 Honor Roll
text: Posted Oct. 19, 2015 at 6:57 PM Updated Oct 19, 2015 at 8:22 PM Posted Oct. 19, 2015 at 6:57 PM Updated Oct 19, 2015 at 8:22 PM High School Football Week 7 Honor Roll West Canada Valley quarterback Josh Chapin rushed for 107 yards and a touchdown – raising his season totals to 1,088 yards and 12 touchdowns – as the Indians captured the Class D East title outright win a win at Westmoreland. Sauquoit Valley’s Andy Castelletti completed 7 of 10 passes for 225 yards and two touchdowns as the first-place Indians ran their NFF East record to 4-0. Oriskany’s Shamis Lasher ran for 160 yards and two touchdowns in a win over Hannibal. Herkimer’s Antonio Aceto rushed for 182 yards on 15 carries, including touchdown runs of 57 and 9 yards, as the Magicians clinched a playoff berth. Mount Markham’s Collin Maine ran for 193 yards and two touchdowns and threw a touchdown pass and Brenton Bond ran for 101 yards and two touchdowns and threw a touchdown pass as the Mustangs clinched a playoff berth. New Hartford’s Dominick Pfisterer ran for two touchdowns and threw touchdown passes to brothers Ryan and Joe Murray as the Spartans won their second straight game. Oneida’s Josh Hood caught touchdown passes of 27 and 42 yards in a Class B East win over Camden. Vernon-Verona-Sherrill’s Brandon Spaven ran for 173 yards and a touchdown and Sean Galla scored on runs of 58 and 36 yards and also had 10 tackles in a Class B East win over Mexico. Notre Dame’s Kinsey Williams rushed for 172 yards on 18 carries, including touchdown runs of 56 and 52 yards, and Nick Sullivan caught a touchdown pass and had two more interceptions as the Class C East champs won their sixth straight game. Waterville’s Nick Salm caught a touchdown pass and also had an interception in a 14-13 win over New York Mills. Westmoreland’s Noah Bowen had 15 tackles in a 7-6 loss to West Canada Valley. Little Falls QB Derek Raux threw touchdown passes to Preston Trumbull and Andy Mucica and Mucica also recovered a fumble for another score in a 22-16 win over Adirondack. Uticaod Posted Oct. 19, 2015 at 6:57 PM Updated Oct 19, 2015 at 8:22 PM
